{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_20","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/experiment_orchestration_notes/FW-M15-001_rationale.md | sed -n '1,90p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\t# FW-M15-001 Rationale\n     2\t\n     3\t## Design Choices\n     4\t\n     5\tThis ticket adds one library-owned Milestone 15 contract module instead of\n     6\tletting suite vocabulary drift across shell scripts, ad hoc result folders, or\n     7\tlater reporting code. The module owns:\n     8\t\n     9\t- the canonical experiment-dimension IDs\n    10\t- the first required ablation-family IDs\n    11\t- suite-cell lineage kinds\n    12\t- work-item status semantics\n    13\t- artifact-role discovery hooks for upstream manifests and downstream bundles\n    14\t- suite-level reproducibility hooks\n    15\t- normalization of representative suite metadata\n    16\t\n    17\tThe contract deliberately composes with the existing Milestone 9 through\n    18\tMilestone 14 layers instead of re-litigating them. The suite layer references\n    19\t`simulation_plan.v1`, `simulator_result_bundle.v1`,\n    20\t`experiment_analysis_bundle.v1`, `validation_ladder.v1`, and\n    21\t`dashboard_session.v1`; it does not replace those contracts.\n    22\t\n    23\tThe ownership boundary is also encoded directly in the contract metadata:\n    24\t\n    25\t- Jack owns the orchestration surface and deterministic mechanics\n    26\t- Grant owns which ablation families and parameterizations are scientifically\n    27\t  meaningful\n    28\t\n    29\tThat keeps the suite layer honest. The software contract defines how ablations\n    30\tare named and tracked, not which scientific claims they prove.\n    31\t\n    32\t## Why The Ticket Stops Before Full Suite Packaging\n    33\t\n    34\tMilestone 15 still has later tickets for planning, execution, packaging,\n    35\taggregation, and reporting. This ticket therefore freezes vocabulary and\n    36\tmetadata hooks first, but it does not invent a premature suite-bundle layout\n    37\tthat would overlap with `FW-M15-005`.\n    38\t\n    39\tThe design-note language is intentional:\n    40\t\n    41\t- suite metadata is already the discovery anchor\n    42\t- upstream bundle paths remain owned by earlier milestone contracts\n    43\t- later suite packaging must reuse the artifact roles and lineage semantics\n    44\t  defined here\n    45\t\n    46\tThat gives the rest of the milestone one stable vocabulary without collapsing\n    47\tseveral later tickets into this first contract ticket.\n    48\t\n    49\t## Testing Strategy\n    50\t\n    51\tThe regression coverage stays focused on the contract surface introduced here:\n    52\t\n    53\t- deterministic normalization and JSON serialization of the Milestone 15 suite\n    54\t  contract metadata\n    55\t- stable discovery of canonical dimension IDs and ablation-family IDs\n    56\t- normalization of representative suite metadata with reordered inputs and\n    57\t  humanized IDs\n    58\t- deterministic suite metadata serialization plus discovery of lineage-linked\n    59\t  cells, work items, and artifact references\n    60\t\n    61\tThis is narrow by design. The ticket is meant to lock vocabulary and metadata\n    62\tsemantics first, not to pretend the full orchestration runner already exists.\n    63\t\n    64\t## Simplifications\n    65\t\n    66\tThe first version intentionally does not implement:\n    67\t\n    68\t- suite-manifest parsing or expansion rules\n    69\t- batch execution or resume logic\n    70\t- ablation transform realizations\n    71\t- suite-owned output-root packaging and result indexing\n    72\t- aggregation, tables, plots, or review-report generation logic\n    73\t\n    74\tIt also uses one minimal suite metadata shape:\n    75\t\n    76\t- upstream references\n    77\t- normalized suite cells\n    78\t- stage-level work items\n    79\t- downstream artifact references\n    80\t\n    81\tThat is enough to freeze the vocabulary Jack and Grant need to share before the\n    82\tlater workflow tickets land.\n    83\t\n    84\t## Future Expansion Points\n    85\t\n    86\tThe clearest follow-on paths are:\n    87\t\n    88\t- `FW-M15-002`: resolve suite manifests and sweep rules into normalized plans\n    89\t- `FW-M15-003`: add deterministic work scheduling and persisted execution state\n    90\t- `FW-M15-004`: realize each ablation family as deterministic transforms\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
