{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_21","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/experiment_orchestration_notes/FW-M15-005_rationale.md | sed -n '20,48p'\"","aggregated_output":"    20\twithout relocating the earlier milestone bundles that already have their own\n    21\tcontracts.\n    22\t\n    23\tThe package layer deliberately composes with the existing Milestone 9 through 14\n    24\tcontracts instead of replacing them.\n    25\t\n    26\t- simulator, analysis, validation, and dashboard bundles stay on their\n    27\t  contract-owned paths\n    28\t- the suite package records references back to those bundle paths\n    29\t- reviewer-facing tables in the package are inventories, not competing bundle\n    30\t  summaries\n    31\t\n    32\tI also kept the distinction between planned targets and realized artifacts\n    33\texplicit. The suite planner already emits planned per-cell stage targets, but\n    34\tthose are not the authoritative answer for realized bundle locations. The\n    35\tpackage therefore records both:\n    36\t\n    37\t- the planned stage output root and planned metadata path from the suite plan\n    38\t- the realized workspace root, stage status, and discovered downstream\n    39\t  artifacts from execution state\n    40\t\n    41\tThat is important because simulation, analysis, validation, and dashboard stages\n    42\twrite into their own earlier-contract layouts under the shared workspace rather\n    43\tthan into the planner’s placeholder metadata paths.\n    44\t\n    45\tAnother deliberate choice is that base and ablation cells carry explicit\n    46\tsimulation-lineage references. Analysis, validation, and dashboard work items\n    47\tbelong to `base_condition` and `ablation_variant` cells, while the simulator\n    48\tbundles live under child `seed_replicate` and `seeded_ablation_variant` cells.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
